description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ipswich Hospital is offering an exciting opportunity for 2 physiologists specialising in echocardiography to join our friendly team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The department offers a full echo service including routine transthoracic studies, contrast, bubble, transoesophageal echo, stress echo (both Dobutamine and Exercise) and physiologist led valve clinics.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In addition to this, we offer a wide range of invasive and non-invasive diagnostics tests, including ECGs, ambulatory monitoring, exercise tolerance testing and device follow ups. Invasive procedures are performed in the new purpose built Heart Centre and include diagnostic angiography, PCI and device implantation.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applications for these posts are invited from experienced, BSE accredited physiologists who wish to advance their clinical and leadership skills.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This post provides an excellent opportunity to help develop and expand our echocardiography services as part of a dynamic and cohesive team.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have weekly review and teaching meetings attended by our imaging consultants and cardiac physiologists.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We actively encourage all our physiologists to develop themselves as individuals by attending relevant clinical courses and participating in wellbeing initiatives.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Informal visits are welcomed and highly recommended prior to interview.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Samantha Clare, Principal Cardiac Physiologist, 01473 703186 - samantha.clarke@esneft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
